Global Funds Sell Net 9.85 Billion Rupees of Indian Derivatives

-- B y   P a r e s h   J a t a k i a
-- 
2011-04-13T03:32:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-13/global-funds-sell-net-9-85-billion-rupees-of-indian-derivatives.html
Global investors sold a net 9.85
billion rupees ($221 million) of Indian equity  derivatives  on
April 11, according to the National Stock Exchange.  Open interest, or the number of contracts outstanding in
value terms, rose 1 percent to 928.9 billion rupees, or 35.6
percent of the gross market position, according to the
exchangeâ€™s website. Open interest reached a record 1.6 trillion
rupees on Sept. 21.  Foreign funds sold a net 6.91 billion rupees of shares in
the  cash  segment on April 11, according to preliminary data
given by the bourse.  To contact the reporter on this story:
